      "died_year": 1931,
      "bio": "Parker Woodward was a solicitor, born in Nottingham on 8 June 1855, the son of John George Woodward (b.1829) and Mary Woodward (b.1825). John George was a partner in the local timber merchants Woodward Clark & Co. of Castle Road Wharf — his partner William Clark(e) and his son William Froggatt Clark were also Park residents. Parker had at least 3 younger siblings: Walter (b.1857), Frank (b.1859), and Mabel Mary (b.1860). Frank lived for many years in Redcliffe on Cavendish Road East.\n\nParker married Maria Renals, sister of John Renals (Alderman and Mayor of Nottingham) and Sir Joseph Renals (Lord Mayor of London 1894–95). Their son Cyril Renals Woodward was named after the Renals family. Parker lived at 25 Cavendish Road East from at least 1891 until his death in 1931, practising as a solicitor throughout.",
